args: Ohmigosh, GUYS—wasn't that concert\nsooooo much fun?
Next time we do a show, will you all\njoin me on stage?
Totally! You remember how Cleo and\nVerica were my backup dancers, right?
That was LITERALLY the best!\nWay more fun than being up there solo!
I must say that I enjoyed it as well.
I found it quite stressful, in truth... But it\nwas certainly a memorable experience.
I'm SAYING! Which is why we should add\neven MORE people next time. More people\nequals more fun—it's basic math!
Is there even room enough on stage\nfor us all to appear at once?
Sure—but I had something else in mind.\nHee hee!
I was thiiiinkiiiing... What if everyone\ndid their own solo performances?!
Ya talkin' about some sorta variety show?
Oh yeah, count me in for that!
Hell, count me in too.\nNow, what'll I perform...
Thanks for coming, everyone!\nI hope you're all ready to have\na ball and a half!
Heh, no way you're ready for\nTHESE muscles!
Ooo, an acrobatic performance—\nWITH swimsuits! See, this is what\nI'm talking about!
The point of said costumes is lost on me,\nbut yes, ＂hooraaaaaay＂...
All right folks, here we go!\nHit it, Ranzal!
You're about to feel this song right\nin yer guts!
Haaaaaaam, succulent soul foooooood!\nYou briiiiing, me tooooo, my kneeeees!
Grounds for going vegetarian, yes.\nWould someone PLEASE put a stop to this?
Hey, come on, we're just gettin' to my\nfavorite part! I said HAAAAAAAAAAAAM—
Er, put your hands together for our\nnext act!
Do you have something good planned?
You better believe it! Not that there was\nanything wrong with Ranzal and Luca's\nidea, mind you.
It merely failed to adequately consider\nthe audience.

Passion is great, but only if it has
somewhere to go. The audience
needs to feel involved! They need
something interactive!
Interesting. Celliera does train knights\nprofessionally, so I imagine she is\nwell-versed in such concepts.
Well, she's got MY attention!\nDrop some knowledge on me, Celly.
What, you thought the performance\nwas over?! Not by a long shot, folks!
It's my honor to introduce you to our\narmsmaster extraordinaire... CELLIERA!
Listen up, kiddos!\nDo you want to be STRONG?!
Do you want to get SWOLE?!\nDo you want to sculpt your body\ninto the STUFF OF LEGENDS?!
Then let's! Get! TRAINING!\nWe'll start with some stretches.\nFollow along, kiddos!
Huh? What's wrong with ＂Celliera's\nHardcore Training Hour, featuring Ranzal\nand Luca＂?
Why's it always muscles with you guys?\nWhere's the like, variety?
Quite right. People attend these shows\nto witness beauty, not muscles.
As a Paladyn, I am fully prepared to\nput forth a masterful performance!
The heck does bein' a Paladyn have to do\nwith performing?
Welcome to Midsummer Paladyns\nOn-Stage! Let us begin, Elisanne!
Yes! May our music reverberate\nthrough the summer sky!

(Heh, you bet we are! This is what show
business is all about, folks! How could
anyone resist the dazzling duet of Elly
and I?)

(We traverse the dance floor with the same
grace we do the battlefield. And it goes
without saying that we know how to get
people's hearts aflutter!)
(Now, with their guards lowered,\nwe'll flash them a smile so refulgent\nit turns their hearts to mush and—huh?!)
(Oh, Goddess... Their stares! Ravenous\neyes abound, fiercer even than any I've\nwitnessed in battle!)
Julietta? What's wrong?\nYou look very pale.
I-I'm fine... I would never embarrass\nyou on stage like—OWWWW!
I think you had better rest a spell.\nHere, come with me.
I think she just stressed herself out\nimagining her performance.
Her anxiety is understandable. Just think,\nperforming before all of those people...\nAnd in a swimsuit, no less!
Yes, such indecency should not\nbe permitted!
There could be children in the audience.\nWe have to ensure the show is\nappropriately wholesome!

Parading about in swimsuits is risqué
enough on its own, but to pile an added
layer of sex appeal on top is... It's simply
too much!
Training's sounding pretty good now, eh?\nNothing more wholesome than a family\nsweating together!
No, no, that's too much! What if somebody\npulls something, or gets heatstroke?
You're all off base. Allow me to show\nyou what a true all-ages show entails!
Welcome, one and all, to Sing-Along\nTime with Miss Estelle and\nMr. {player_name}!
Okay, everybody on your feet!\nJust follow my moves, and we'll\nall have a great time!

We're going to put our right hands in,
and then we're going to pull them back
out, and then we're going to put them
BACK in, and shake them! Everyone ready?
Hold up just a second there!
What? Why?\nIs this not perfectly wholesome?
Oh, sure, it's wholesome all right.\nIt's just... How do I put this?
We're tryin' to entertain people here,\nnot send 'em back to preschool, yeah?
Your idea does sound like it may be\nsomewhat...tedious for older audiences.
Hmm... I guess you have a point.\nIt's pretty difficult to come up with\nsomething everyone can enjoy...
Yeah, I had no clue this'd be such\na headache. I just wanted to\nsing my ham song...
This may not be a puzzle we can\nsolve in a day.

You might be right. It really puts into
perspective how incredible it was that
those three managed to make everyone
happy with their concert.
We didn't do it alone—every one of you\nhelped make it possible!
As far as I'm concerned, you ALL starred\nin that show. You feel me?

Hee hee! And, to show you how super
de-DUPER thankful I am, I'm gonna put
on a secret concert for all of you—like,
literally right now!
We should go fetch Verica and Julietta.
Siren, why don't you get set up while\nwe're gone?
Okay, everyone, it's time to get LOUD!
